UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1275
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION establishing the Charitable Gaming
2 Modernization Task Force to study, review, and report on updates to Kentucky’s
3 charitable gaming statutes and administrative regulations.
4 WHEREAS, charitable gaming has long served as a critical fundraising mechanism
5 for nonprofit organizations throughout the Commonwealth, including faith-based
6 organizations, public and private schools, veterans’ organizations, volunteer fire
7 departments, fraternal organizations, and other charitable and civic entities; and
8 WHEREAS, proceeds from charitable gaming support essential community
9 services, charitable missions, and public-benefit activities that would otherwise require
10 additional public or private funding; and
11 WHEREAS, Kentucky’s charitable gaming framework is governed primarily by
12 KRS Chapters 230 and 238 and their accompanying administrative regulations, which
13 together comprise an extensive, highly technical, and complex regulatory scheme; and
14 WHEREAS, recent organizational and structural changes to the oversight of
15 charitable gaming within state government underscore the importance of ensuring that
16 Kentucky’s statutory and regulatory framework is clear, coherent, and aligned with
17 modern administrative practices; and
18 WHEREAS, a thoughtful review of charitable gaming laws and administrative
19 regulations may identify opportunities to responsibly enhance charitable revenues while
20 maintaining strong safeguards for integrity, transparency, accountability, and public trust,
21 and may assist policymakers in clearly distinguishing lawful charitable gaming from
22 unlawful or unregulated activities;
23 NOW, THEREFORE,
24 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
25 Commonwealth of Kentucky, the Senate concurring therein:
26 Section 1. The Legislative Research Commission is hereby directed to establish
27 the Charitable Gaming Modernization Task Force. The task force shall study Kentucky’s
Page 1 of 3
