UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1275
1 charitable gaming laws and administrative regulations and accomplish the following:
2 (1) Complete a comprehensive statutory and regulatory review identifying
3 redundancies, inconsistencies, and obsolete provisions within KRS Chapters 230 and 238
4 and their associated administrative regulations;
5 (2) Consider stakeholder input from licensed charitable organizations across
6 multiple categories, including faith-based, educational, veterans, public safety, and other
7 nonprofit entities;
8 (3) Compare charitable gaming regulatory frameworks in peer or similarly
9 situated states;
10 (4) Review administrative and technological processes related to charitable
11 gaming licensure; and
12 (5) Recommend statutory or regulatory changes, as appropriate.
13 Section 2. The Charitable Gaming Modernization Task Force shall consist of
14 the following ten members, with final membership of the task force being subject to the
15 consideration and approval of the Legislative Research Commission:
16 (1) Four members of the House of Representatives appointed by the Speaker of
17 the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be designated by the Speaker of the
18 House of Representatives as a co-chair of the task force;
19 (2) One member of the House of Representatives appointed by the Minority Floor
20 Leader of the House of Representatives;
21 (3) Four members of the Senate appointed by the President of the Senate, one of
22 whom shall be designated by the President of the Senate as a co-chair of the task force;
23 and
24 (4) One member of the Senate appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of the
25 Senate.
26 Section 3. The Charitable Gaming Modernization Task Force shall meet at least
27 four times during the 2026 Interim and shall submit its findings, legislative
Page 2 of 3
XXXX 3/4/2026 12:24 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1275
1 recommendations, or a memorandum to the Legislative Research Commission no later
2 than December 1, 2026. If legislative recommendations are submitted, the Legislative
3 Research Commission may refer the recommendations to the appropriate committee or
4 committees of jurisdiction in advance of the 2027 Regular Session of the Kentucky
5 General Assembly.
6 Section 4. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
7 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
8 issues identified herein to an interim joint committee or subcommittee thereof, and to
9 designate a study completion date.
